# speckit-linear — example environment file
#
# The default integration path uses the official Linear MCP at
# https://mcp.linear.app via OAuth, which stores its refresh token in
# Claude Code's OAuth cache (~/.mcp-auth/) and requires NO secret in this
# repository.
#
# The variables below are only needed if you opt into the fallback path —
# e.g. running the workspace seed against a Linear workspace where the
# official MCP cannot create custom workflow states, in which case the
# bridge uses Linear's GraphQL API directly with a personal API key.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values only on machines that
# need the fallback path. `.env` is gitignored.

# Personal Linear API key (https://linear.app/settings/api). Only required
# for the workspace-seed GraphQL helper. Leave unset for normal sync.
# LINEAR_API_KEY=

# Linear workspace identifier this repo is bound to. Optional override —
# normally read from .specify/extensions/linear/config.yml inside each
# consumer repo.
# LINEAR_WORKSPACE_ID=

# Linear team identifier that owns the repo-Projects. Optional override.
# LINEAR_TEAM_ID=
